{"componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-boattemplate-jsx", "path": "/boat/2683", "result": {"pageContext": {"absolute": "https://oga.org.uk", "boat": {"builder": [{"id": "3bce15f6-ee0f-46a9-a70d-a8cead71eda4", "name": "Gaffers and Luggers"}], "construction_material": "grp", "created_at": "2020-04-25T17:24:28.267927+00:00", "design_class": {"id": "47040682-ee05-42de-a493-400ebd5956db", "name": "Heard 28"}, "designer": [{"id": "7ac480da-7d09-4dd7-9c89-61199ff30913", "name": "Percy Dalton"}], "for_sales": [{"created_at": "2020-02-16T19:04:46+00:00", "flexibility": "normal", "reduced": false, "sales_text": "<p>Hull built 1984, 28\u2019 LOD, c. 5\u2019 draught. Gaff cutter with large `racing\u2019 rig,\nstowable bowsprit c. 13.5\u2019. Originally built for racing, sail number (42) is\nFalmouth racing number. Cabin added later for cruising use. GRP hull, epoxy\ncoated below waterline, copper coated, wooden decks and coach roof. Four berths\nin two cabins, galley with Taylor\u2019s paraffin cooker (2 hob and oven) and sink,\nchart table, hanging locker, heads, diesel cabin heater. Range of sails\nincluding topsail. Perkins Perama M30 Diesel engine with new gearbox 2012.\nTaylor\u2019s 079D diesel cabin heater, Jabsco manual toilet. Currently lying ashore,\nEssex. ?</p>", "updated_at": "2020-05-03T10:13:13.309954+00:00"}], "generic_type": ["Yacht"], "handicap_data": {"beam": 3.048, "draft": 1.524, "fore_triangle_base": 6.315532796878809, "fore_triangle_height": 9.616556937332359, "length_on_deck": 8.5344, "length_on_waterline": 8.077298219946353, "length_over_all": 8.53450377956596, "length_over_spars": 12.649353816142403, "main": {"foot": 6.059497683491831, "head": 5.5992440868080955, "luff": 5.263960009753718}, "propellor": {"type": "fixed"}, "thcf": 1.010023851, "topsail": {"luff": 7.071445988783223, "perpendicular": 7.924896366739819}}, "home_country": "GBR", "home_port": "Sussex Yacht Club, Shoreham", "hull_form": "long keel deep forefoot", "id": "aedc8c07-cb